Reasoning: The paper deals with the impact of oscillator phase noise on communication system performance, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-disciplines. The most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper derives a statistical model and analyzes the impact of phase noise on the error vector magnitude (EVM) of communication systems. The second likely category is cs.COMM (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper deals with the performance of communication systems. The third likely category is cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper deals with the modeling and analysis of a system. The fourth likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture), as the paper deals with the impact of noise on communication systems. The fifth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia), as the paper deals with the impact of noise on the quality of multimedia signals.
